<item>
 <title>Radio Interview:  « Le Grand Témoin », Radio Notre-Dame</title>
 <link>https://marinelepen.sites.stanford.edu/radio-interview-%C2%AB-le-grand-t%C3%A9moin-%C2%BB-radio-notre-dame</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Journalist Louis Daufresnes interviews Cécile Alduy in &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://radionotredame.net/emission/le-grand-temoin/18-03-2015/&quot;&gt;Le Grand Témoin&lt;/a&gt;&quot; about the elusive nature of political concepts, their plasticity and who gets to define their pragmatic meaning in  society.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;In this 28-minute vivid conversation, we look at how national sentiment in the Renaissance emerged as a dynamic competition and emulation with other countries rather than a rigid definition of the identity of a people, and compare Marine Le Pen&#039;s discourse with that of other political figures. And yes, we even talk about hypotyposis!&lt;/p&gt;
